# Velorex Design — database credentials template
#
# DO NOT commit a real .env file. This .env.example is the template only.
# The project-root .htaccess blocks public HTTP access to .env, but the real
# danger is committing it to git — which is why .env is in .gitignore.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SETUP ON HOSTINGER
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. hPanel → Databases → Management
#    - Note your DB name, DB username, and DB password
#    - If none exists, click "Create new database" first
#
# 2. hPanel → File Manager → public_html/  (the project root, next to index.html)
#    - Top-right gear icon → tick "Show hidden files"
#    - Right-click .env.example → Copy
#    - Rename the copy to exactly ".env" (just .env — no .txt, nothing else)
#    - Open .env and replace the four REPLACE_ME values below
#    - Save
#
# 3. Visit https://your-domain.com/api/setup.php once
#    - This creates all tables and seeds admin "owner" / "owner123"
#    - Response should be {"success": true, ...}
#
# 4. Log in at admin.html with owner / owner123
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# RULES FOR THE .env FILE
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   - No quotes around values:        DB_PASS=secret      ✓
#                                     DB_PASS="secret"    ✗
#   - No spaces around =:             DB_USER=u123_x      ✓
#                                     DB_USER = u123_x    ✗
#   - File must be in the project root, next to index.html
#     (the legacy api/.env path is still read as a fallback)
#   - Lines starting with # are comments and are ignored

DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USER=REPLACE_ME_with_your_db_user
DB_PASS=REPLACE_ME_with_your_db_password
DB_NAME=REPLACE_ME_with_your_db_name
